class Solution {
    public String answerString(String word, int numFriends) {
        int n = word.length();
        if (numFriends == 1) return word;
        int maxLen = n - numFriends + 1;
        String best = "";
        for (int i = 0; i + maxLen <= n; ++i) {
            String cand = word.substring(i, i + maxLen);
            if (cand.compareTo(best) > 0) best = cand;
        }
        return best;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The lexicographically largest substring that can appear in any split is the maximum-length prefix of the longest possible segment, which is simply the maximum substring of length n - numFriends + 1.

